"Oh, about that..." - Dr. Anthony Fauci

Their idea was more correct than the opposite alternative that others were pushing (all your health issues are because of your bad habits like smoking, it's all your fault) even if obv. it would be better if most people could e.g. do windsurfing instead of smoking two packs a day

Big Tobacco sponsored a lot of early research into stress because they were trying to promote the idea stress was the thing making people sick and sick people were more likely to self-medicate by smoking to distract themselves. E.g. they gave money to Hans Selye for his research.

They lost on the scientific battlefield and got wiped out there, but left enough cultural ruins from the war to matter, everyone has the concept of "workplace stress", knows about "your job killing you", etc. Stress research is intimately tied to cigarettes and tobacco industry.
